##############################################

DOCUMENT();

loadMacros(
  "PGstandard.pl",
  "MathObjects.pl",
  "PGML.pl",
  "contextPercent.pl",
  "PGcourse.pl",
);

##############################################

Context("Numeric");

$ans1 = random(2,9,1);
$b = random(200,900,100);
$a1 = $ans1/100*$b;

$ans2 = $ans1/10;
$a2 = $a1/10;

$ans3 = $ans1/100;
$a3 = $a1/100;

Context("LimitedPercent-strict");
Context()->flags->set(
   trimTrailingZeros => 1,
   decimalPlaces => 4,
   tolerance => .00005,
);
$ans1P = Compute("$ans1 %");
$ans2P = Compute("$ans2 %");
$ans3P = Compute("$ans3 %");

##############################################

TEXT(beginproblem());

BEGIN_PGML

Fill in the blanks with percentages:

a)    [`[$a1]`] is [____]{$ans1P} of [` [$b] `]?

b)    [`[$a2]`] is [____]{$ans2P} of [` [$b] `]?

c)    [`[$a3]`] is [____]{$ans3P} of [` [$b] `]?

END_PGML

##############################################

$a100 = $a1*100;
$a200 = $a2*100;
$a300 = $a3*100;

BEGIN_PGML_SOLUTION

This translation from English to math may help you remember the percentage formula.

    [` 2 \text{ is } 50% \text{ of } 4 \Longleftrightarrow 2 = 0.5 \cdot 4 `]

a)  [`[$a1]`] is what [`%`] of [` [$b] `]?

    [`
\begin{aligned}
  [$a1] &= \frac{x}{100} \cdot [$b] \\
  100([$a1]) &= 100\cdot\frac{x}{100}\cdot[$b] \\
  [$a100] &= x\cdot[$b] \\  
  \frac{[$a100]}{[$b]} &= x\\  
  [$ans1] &= x\\
  x &= [$ans1]
\end{aligned}
    `]

    So [`[$a1]`] is [`[$ans1]%`] of [` [$b] `].  
----
b)  [`[$a2]`] is what [`%`] of [` [$b] `]?

    [`
\begin{aligned}
  [$a2] &= \frac{x}{100} \cdot [$b] \\
  100([$a2]) &= 100\cdot\frac{x}{100}\cdot[$b] \\
  [$a200] &= x\cdot[$b] \\  
  \frac{[$a200]}{[$b]} &= x\\  
  [$ans2] &= x\\
  x &= [$ans2]
\end{aligned}
    `]

    So [`[$a2]`] is [`[$ans2]%`] of [` [$b] `].  
----
c)  [`[$a3]`] is what [`%`] of [` [$b] `]?

    [`
\begin{aligned}
  [$a3] &= \frac{x}{100} \cdot [$b] \\
  100([$a3]) &= 100\cdot\frac{x}{100}\cdot[$b] \\
  [$a300] &= x\cdot[$b] \\  
  \frac{[$a300]}{[$b]} &= x\\  
  [$ans3] &= x\\
  x &= [$ans3]
\end{aligned}
    `]

    So [`[$a3]`] is [`[$ans3]%`] of [` [$b] `].  


END_PGML_SOLUTION

